places.perex: Located on the seafront, this golf club provides its visitors with great views. Its 18 holes are quite challenging.

places.name: The Mall Cineplex

places.name: Our Lady of the Assumption Church
places.perex: Although Brunei is prevalently Islamic, you can also find a Catholic church here. Come here for an English mass!

places.name: Thann Sanctuary Spa
places.perex: Claimed to be one of the best spas in the world, this center offers amazing range of treatments together in a serene environment.

places.name: Seri Kenangan Beach
places.perex: Pantai Seri Kenangan - literally, the "unforgettable beach" - is in Kuala Tutong in Tutong District.

places.name: Muara Beach
places.perex: More than 1.5 kilometres long, this sandy beach makes for a pleasant day out. It is pretty well-equipped, suitable for families.

places.name: Kuala Belalong Field Study Centre
places.perex: Brunei is known for its diverse vegetation and this center focuses on the local rainforests. Enjoy your jungle adventure here!

places.name: Brunei Proboscis Monkey River Safari
places.perex: Have you ever seen a proboscis monkey? You have a great opportunity to watch this strange animal during the boat tour!

places.name: Tasek Lama Recreational Park
places.perex: You'll feel like in the jungle while walking around this park. Admire its waterfall and hike the trekking trail!

places.name: The Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf
places.perex: You can choose from an amazing range of tea and coffee kinds at this café. Taste its specialties such as pomelo tea!

places.name: Royal Ceremonial Hall
places.perex: Hosting various royal ceremonies, this building is a gem of the city center. Note the ceiling with a golden dome!

places.name: Oil & Gas Discovery Centre
places.perex: Find out about the secret of gas extraction and oil production in the interactive exhibitions of this centre.

places.name: Yayasan Sultan Haji Hassanal Bolkiah Complex
places.perex: A huge complex of buildings including not only schools but also a popular shopping mall. You can buy clothes, jewellery and other items here.

places.name: Kianggeh Open Air Market
places.perex: Established in the 1960s, this market has been providing its customers with the freshest local produce. Buy some shrimps or vegetables here!

places.name: Excapade Sushi
places.perex: An exquisite Japanese restaurant specializing in sushi. Don't hesitate and try out their mussels and snow crabs, too.

places.name: Mausoleum of Sultan Bolkiah
places.perex: Sultan Bolkiah was a successful ruler who connected new lands to Brunei. This magnificent tomb commemorates him and 39 years of his reign.

places.name: Damuan Recreational Park
places.perex: This long and narrow park is an ideal place for a walk or a morning run. Admire its outdoor sculptures!

places.name: Royal Mausoleum
places.perex: Members of the Brunei royal family, including the last four sultans, are buried at this mausoleum. Come to admire their tombs!

places.name: House of Twelve Roofs
places.perex: Dating back to the beginning of the 20th century, this building used to house British officers. It belongs to the oldest in Brunei.

places.name: Kampong Ayer Cultural & Tourism Gallery
places.perex: Discover the fascinating history of Kampong Ayer in this new gallery. You'll learn more about the local life here.

places.name: Sungai Basong Recreational Park
places.perex: The most interesting feature of this park is its cultural village. You can familiarize yourself with the life of 5 local ethnic groups here.

places.name: Lumut Beach
places.perex: If you want to chill out near the sea, this beach is the right choice for you. There are also many small shops and restaurants around.

places.name: Mausoleum of Sultan Sharif Ali
places.perex: The 4th Sultan of Brunei is buried at this place. Admire the onion-like roof of the tomb, as well as its Arabian design.

places.name: Meragang Beach
places.perex: A tranquil sandy beach surrounded by a dense forest. Watching the sunset at this place is an unforgettable experience.

places.name: Trijaya Equestrian Park
places.perex: Enjoy horseriding on the pathways of the extensive Jerudong park. You can also watch a game of polo here.

places.name: Mercu Dirgahayu 60 Monument
places.perex: Located on the waterfront, this monument celebrates the 60th birthday of the Sultan Haji Hassanal Bolkiah.

places.name: Brunei History Center
places.perex: The interesting history and genealogy of Brunei sultans is presented in a comprehensible way here. Not boring at all!

places.name: Bukit Subok Recreational Park
places.perex: Relax in this well-maintained park from where you can view the capital of Brunei. There is a nice hiking trail around the reserve.

places.name: Serasa Beach
places.perex: Located on a narrow peninsula, this beach is popular with water sports lovers. Offers yachting, windsurfing, jet skiing and more.
